features: EASY PLUG-N-GO CAMERA – Simply connect the USB-A cable to your PC, clip the external webcam to the display, and let the webcam's auto-adjust to your room’s lighting; plus, stay secure with the manual privacy cover and red LED camera-in-use indicator

OPTIMIZED FOR MODERN PLATFORMS – Instantly and easily integrate your USB-A webcam with popular video conferencing platforms, such as Zoom, Microsoft Teams, and other video chat applications.
CUSTOMIZE YOUR SETUP – Find the perfect angle for your next video conference with this webcam’s laptop display or desktop monitor clip mount, 360-degree swivel, and support for tripod mounting (2).

body.description: Look and sound great on any video chat or meeting with the HP 320 FHD Webcam with microphone. Hopping on a live video meeting, collaborating with colleagues, or just chatting with family and friends takes just seconds with this easy-to-use USB webcam. Simply plug in the USB-A cable to your laptop or PC monitor, clip the webcam to your display with the adjustable mount, and then sit back as your webcam auto-adjusts to the ambient light of your environment so you can focus on what matters. Conversations between colleagues or family members feel natural thanks to the Full HD 1080p webcam’s wide field of view (1), perfect for accurately showing you, your room, or anyone else who wants to sit in. No need to download and configure special software—this webcam for laptop and desktop computers is ready for Zoom, Microsoft Teams, and other video chat applications. Fine tune your web conferencing setup for the perfect angle with the webcam’s adjustable clip mount that easily attaches to your display or almost anywhere, no tools required. Plus, your wide-angle webcam’s 360-degree swivel and support for camera tripod mounts provides even more streaming or conferencing flexibility (2). Work, chat, or stream with confidence as this PC camera works seamlessly with your Chromebook and other Chrome OS devices (3) (4) and includes a manual privacy cover and red LED camera-in-use indicator to keep things secure and private. (1) Actual resolution may vary to network, system and other requirements. (2) Tripod not included. (3) Google tested to meet Chromebook compatibility standards.​ (4) This product works with devices capable of running the latest version of Chrome OS and has been certified to meet Google's compatibility standards. Google is not responsible for the operation of this product or its compliance with safety requirements. Chromebook and the Works With Chromebook badge are trademarks of Google LLC.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great compact camera
reviews.reviewText: For around $30, this is a great little camera. Picture quality is excellent. Nice wide-angle viewing. Just plug it in and you're off and running. It is fixed focus but what do you want for the price. It's small enough to throw in you luggage and take it with you when traveling. I didn't need a camera with a lot of bells and whistles. Just a camera for occasional video calls. Only issue on the installation was I expected an icon to pop up on my desktop or apps list. I had to get into my device list, find the camera and turn it on before it showed up in my app list. (Windows 11)Would I buy this camera again? Absolutely. If you're looking for simple, compact, inexpensive, great image, this might fit your bill.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good camera for video calls
reviews.reviewText: bought this camera in a rush to replace my old logitech that failed. works good and high quality and works on all video apps (obs, discord, WhatsApp, etc). i bought the cosmetically flawed version and it still looked fairly good, just was sort of dusty and had a dinged up box but still great value for money. only issue i have is it has a fairly dim light on the bottom when it's on, although that might just be my model or something

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great camera, but not very secure
reviews.reviewText: Camera quality is great and it was extremely easy to connect. My only complaint is that the camera doesn't perch very securely on top of my monitor. I was hoping for a little more tension to be on the arm that opens to help wedge the camera onto the top of the monitor frame. It's really just balancing on the top, so if you adjust your monitor of bump the cord, it shifts out of position or falls off. Not great for someone who has a desk or monitors they like to adjust and need the camera to stay put.

reviews.reviewText: Es una excelente opción para quienes no cuentan con cámara en su computadora, recomiendo ampliamente, me gusta que tiene una tapa para la privacidad y se puede montar fácilmente en el monitor.
